Welcome to our blog section
We’ve all been dying to know which type of magic the Gaines would bring to the café, a landmark on Waco’s bustling traffic circle that closed down in February of 2016. The Fixer Upper stars’ Magnolia brand, which includes the Magnolia Market, a premium interior paint line, a bakery, and a quarterly home magazine, has already reshaped the culture and perception of Waco, Texas.

Known as the French reporter
Jackie
Introducing Jackie, known as the French reporter-turned-owner of Jackie Brick House eatery in Monticello, Florida. With her background as a former entertainer and renowned red carpet host, she brings a touch of glamour to the dining experience. Alongside the talented chefs Rowdy Ryan and Vic Daddy, they create extraordinary culinary creations that captivate and entertain. Infusing their dishes with creativity and flair, each plate tells a unique story. Prepare to embark on a delectable journey where food becomes a form of entertainment, curated by our talented owner and her exceptional crew. Welcome to a dining experience like no other.
Professional Cuban lead dancer
Jorge the Artist
The professional Cuban lead dancer of the Tallahassee Ballet, has joined forces with Jackie, the esteemed Hollywood celebrity red carpet host, who is also known as the French reporter. Together, they have embarked on an exciting venture to open a delightful breakfast and lunch restaurant. Their vision was to create a lively gathering place where people could come together regularly, and their dream has become a reality.
Introducing Local Favorites, a charming and cozy establishment where locals eagerly share their stories of joy, pain, and family. Jorge, known for his meticulous nature, attends to every detail, ensuring impeccable service to his beloved customers. When he’s not greeting guests in the dining room, you’ll find him in the kitchen, where his salads have become the talk of the town. Just like his dancing, everything Jorge creates is perfection, meticulously crafted and presented.
But Jorge’s talents extend beyond dance and culinary expertise—he possesses an incredible singing voice that captivates all who hear it. The moment he begins to sing, people flock to gather and eagerly listen, their whispers of admiration and excitement filling the air. The locals truly appreciate the opportunity to be hosted by such a remarkably talented artist.
A visit to Jackie’s Brickhouse guarantees a joyful and fulfilling experience. The combination of Jorge’s artistic prowess and Jackie’s warm hospitality creates an atmosphere that will leave you feeling uplifted and content. Come and immerse yourself in the happiness that awaits you at this extraordinary establishment.
Lead chef
Rowdy Ryan
Our lead chef with a perpetual rowdy mood that adds a unique flair to his culinary creations. Despite his lively demeanor, he never compromises on flavor. Passionate and dedicated, he refuses to cut corners, always delivering his best. Rowdy goes the extra mile to ensure your satisfaction, leaving no stone unturned in crafting a memorable dining experience. With Rowdy in the kitchen, you can expect exceptional flavors and a lively culinary journey.
Chef
Vic Daddy
Meet Chef Vic Daddy, the patriarch of our warm and inviting family-oriented restaurant. In the kitchen, he takes charge and demands perfection in every aspect. With his meticulous attention to detail, everything must be flawless. For Vic, the sous chefs' assistance is crucial—it's a do-or-die situation. They must diligently follow his lead to ensure impeccable results for our beloved customers and friends. With Chef Vic Daddy at the helm, our restaurant promises an atmosphere of excellence and culinary delights.
Turning chaos into order
Arivel Cortes
A decade ago, Arivel Cortes, a native from the bustling streets of Curban, journeyed to the land of opportunity in pursuit of her dreams. Possessing an angelic voice capable of touching souls, she also had an extraordinary talent for organization, turning chaos into order with almost magical ease.
When Jackie, the proprietor of Jackie's Brickhouse Eatery, learned from her business partner and Arivel's brother, Jorge Arceo, that his talented sister was now residing in Florida, she immediately knew she had found a missing piece of her puzzle. Without a moment's hesitation, Jackie extended an invitation for Arivel to join the Brickhouse team.
Arivel saw this as a golden opportunity: not only could she earn a living while working alongside her brother, but she could also infuse her passion for singing and organization into keeping Jackie's Brickhouse in impeccable shape.
Two years into this harmonious partnership, Arivel has become the beating heart of the establishment. She adores sharing her life with the customers who frequent Jackie's Brickhouse, serenading them with her melodies and lighting up their faces with smiles. Indeed, anyone who steps into Jackie's Brickhouse is graced by Arivel's unique blend of talents, leaving with both their bellies and souls nourished.
